T|Funn|0|The standard funnel dashboard shows a horizontal or vertical funnel graphic w/ drop-off rates btw each stage, plus a conversion rate tn chart showing week-over-week improvement. Key in: the drop-off btw add-to-cart and purchase is the highest-leverage area for most DTC brands.
T|Funn|1|
T|Funn|2|---
T|Funn|3|
T|Mode|[TABLE:4×6]
T|What|0|Triple Whale's "Triple Attribution" — combines post-purchase surveys ("How did you hear abt us?") w/ px data. Most popular among DTC brands spending $10K-$200K/mo.
T|What|1|Northbeam's MMM (mk Mix Modeling) — uses Bayesian statistics. Preferred by brands spending $100K+/mo across 4+ channels.
T|What|2|Google's Data-Driven Attribution — built into GA4. Free but less accurate for cross-device journeys.
T|What|3|Post-purchase surveys — simple "How did you hear abt us?" survey. Surprisingly accurate for DTC. Often used alongside px-based attribution.
T|What|4|Incrementality testing — geo-based lift tests. Gold standard but expensive and slow.
T|What|5|
T|Reco|0|Use a hybrid approach: last-touch for channel-level reporting (simple, comparable), plus post-purchase survey data for understanding true discovery sources. Don't over-invest in attribution until monthly ad spend exceeds $30K combined.
T|Reco|1|
T|Reco|2|---
T|Reco|3|
